Marana police officer Michael Rapiejko rammed his car into armed robbery suspect Mario Valencia on February 19 . 
  He said he was forced to use deadly force after Valencia fired a shot from a rifle into the air . 
  Officer said he had to 'shoot him or run him over' in interview with investigators . 
  Dash cam footage showed him mounting the curb and mowing down Valencia . 
  Police have defended his actions in Marana, Arizona and said Valencia had left him with no other choice . 
 